Test-case name: fileroller/flr-001
This test will check that File Roller can archive and extract files
<ol>
<li title="action"> Open the dash and launch file-roller by pressing the super key, and then entering ‘file-roller’</li>
<ol>
<li title="expected_result">file-roller should launch</li>
</ol>
<li title="action"> Click 'New' button from the toolbar</li>
<ol>
<li title="expected_result">'New' file save dialog appears</li>
</ol>
<li title="action"> Input any test name for archive, select 'Tar compressed with gzip' from available formats combobox, click 'Create' button</li>
<ol>
<li title="expected_result">A new empty archive with specified name and format is created</li>
</ol>
<li title="action"> Click 'Add files to archive' button from toolbar</li>
<ol>
<li title="expected_result">'Add Files' file open dialog is displayed</li>
</ol>
<li title="action"> Select any files to be added to the archive, click 'Add' button</li>
<ol>
<li title="expected_result">Selected files are displayed in the archive contents list</li>
</ol>
<li title="action"> Click 'Add a folder to archive' button from toolbar</li>
<ol>
<li title="expected_result">'Add a Folder' file open dialog is displayed</li>
</ol>
<li title="action"> Select any non-empty folder to be added to the archive, click 'Add' button</li>
<ol>
<li title="expected_result">Selected folder is displayed in the archive contents list</li>
</ol>
<li title="action"> Close file-roller, open nautilus and navigate to the folder where the archive has been created</li>
<ol>
<li title="expected_result">Archive is present in the folder</li>
</ol>
<li title="action"> Open the archive using file-roller</li>
<ol>
<li title="expected_result">Archive contents is displayed correctly in file-roller</li>
</ol>
<li title="action"> Click 'Extract' button from toolbar</li>
<ol>
<li title="expected_result">'Extract' folder open dialog appears</li>
</ol>
<li title="action"> Select any folder to extract files to, click 'Extract' button</li>
<ol>
<li title="expected_result">Dialog closes. 'Extracting files from archive' dialog appears</li>
</ol>
<li title="action"> Wait until extracting process is complete</li>
<ol>
<li title="expected_result">'Extraction completed successfully' label appears</li>
</ol>
<li title="action"> Open Nautilus and navigate to the selected extract folder</li>
<ol>
<li title="expected_result">Are the files and folders from archive extracted correctly in the selected folder?</li>
</ol>
</ol>
<strong>
If all actions produce the expected results listed, please <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> a 'passed' result.
If an action fails, or produces an unexpected result, please <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> 'failed' and <a href="../../buginstructions">file a bug</a>. Please be sure to include the bug number when you <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> your result</strong>